      "Description": "Take the OriginalDesignConcept.html design template file from the ReportingDashboard repo, as well as the C:/Pics/ReportingDashboardDesign.png design of what I want the dashboard to look like, and create a simple one page webpage which is used to report to executives on a specific project's milestones and progress. This will read the needed data from a json config file called data.json, and take the design and create an example fake data for a fictional project. Follow the example html design and improve upon it to make it the best reporting view for executives to give visibility to a project in terms of how it's going, what was shipped, in progress, carried over from last month, and a timeline at the top of milestones for specific big rocks in the project. Make this super simple, no auth, not enterprise security, just very basic for the functionality needed. Also, be sure all agents read the html design file before building out any plan or code. I want this to be reasonable simple because I will take screenshots of this page (like the simplicity in the original html design) for my Powerpoint decks to executives.",
